			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				-=update=-
<br />

<br />
Ok, the filter is now user-specific. Use of swearing and naughty terms is hereby allowed in all forums. 
<br />

<br />
Also, Tym is coding out people's ability to bypass the filter using bbcode and other breakups. Soon it will be so hard to bypass the filter that nobody will bother to do all the work required.
<br />

<br />
===========================================
<br />

<br />
Ok, so we've got two camps of people on this board at the moment. Camp number one wants to use every dirty deragatory term in the book in the most colorful way possible. Camp number two bleeds from the eyes if they see the word "poo" in a post. Naturally, they don't get along. This has been causing some complaints lately.
<br />

<br />
All forums except for F&amp;R are intended to be censored. F&amp;R is intended to be uncensored and as unmoderated as possible with the sole exception of spam removal and removal of material that can land us in legal hot water. Our profanity filter is global, and cannot exclude specific forums like F&amp;R from its scope despite their uncensored nature.
<br />

<br />
Currently the F&amp;R crowd has been putting up with the censorship, but it's becoming a big pain as we add more and more terms to it. To fix this problem we are adding a new mod to the boards, and I am completely changing the current rules with regards to profanity and racist or other deragatory terms.
<br />

<br />
Tym is installing a mod tonight that makes the profanity filter user-based. Once it is installed, by default, ALL users of this forum will have the profanity filter turned on. You must now opt-out of the profanity filter just like you must opt-in to F&amp;R. The folks who don't want this filter will now have the option to go to their profile and turn it off. There is no selectiveness to the filter in this case. It will block all terms or no terms, and that's the best we can do. If that's not good enough, you'll simply have to cope.
<br />

<br />
Since the profanity filter will be user based, there is no reason to censor any forums. All swearing and racist terms, deragatory terms etc will be allowed in all forums without restriction. Those who don't want to see them won't, and those who do, will. Mods will no longer be responsible for editing posts or taking action against those using harsh language in any part of the board.
<br />

<br />
However...
<br />

<br />
Discussions (except in F&amp;R) still need to be kept civil; pointlessly attacking posts or people is still actionable. Swarming threads with deragatory comments has become a problem of late (especially in R&amp;C), and moderators are going to be taking a more active interest in stopping this sort of thing from happening. If it does happen, expect any inflammatory posts to be deleted outright with no warning and no record of it left behind in the thread (since leaving a record of the disruption also causes a disruption). Mods will warn the offending poster with PMs if it becomes a repeated problem.
<br />

<br />
The word filter is easy to circumvent. There is no longer any need to do this. Any attempts to circumvent the word filter outside of F&amp;R are going to be dealt with very harsly. If you want to use the F word, use it and leave your profanity filter off. Using it and bypassing the filter so that everyone ends up seeing it is going to become a problem for the offender real fast. F&amp;R is of course exempt; posters may circumvent the word filter in there as much as they like.
<br />

<br />
The word filter list is not very populated at the moment. As people find terms that are offensive that should be added to the filter, they should PM the administrators (me, tym, moslad, bic) with a request to add that word to the filter and it will be added. We will not be editing posts from this point on to remove ditry language; it's all going to be done by the word filter. Do not expect moderators to be viewing the forums in their censored state and policing for new terms to add for you. Most of the admin and mod team prefer things unrestricted. We are relying on the normal users to notify us if there is a problem.
<br />

<br />
Please keep in mind that the word filter does not change the content of a post. It is simply a script that runs inside php and replaces them in your page view. All words currently covered by the filter are still there in their original form, and will no longer appear censored once you turn the filter off in your profile.
<br />

<br />
Changes to the written rules to reflect this new policy will be forthcoming.
<br />

<br />
So, to sum up...
<br />

<br />
1) New profanity filter is going in tonight.
<br />
2) Profanity in all of its forms is now allowed in all of the forums without restriction.
<br />
3) You must opt-out of the profanity filter in your profile to see this profanity.
<br />
4) Attempts to circumvent the profanity filter outside of F&amp;R will be dealt with harshly.
<br />
5) This is not a license to attack and swear in every post in every forum.
<br />
6) Those who have issues with a specific word must PM an admin to have it added to the filter.
<br />
7) New terms will not be added to the filter unless someone specifically asks for them to be added.
<br />

<br />
Any questions?<br />
				<span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by EvilNight on Sat Feb 28, 2004 3:22 pm; edited 2 times in total</span><br />
